    public interface IAccept
    This interface is defined and implemented as a marker that the accept method is available and to ensure that subtypes implement the accept method
    Author:
    David Cok

      <T> T accept(IVisitor<T> v)
      The accept method corresponding the IVisitor, to be implemented in each subclass as { return v.visit(this); }

        <T> T accept(IVisitor<T> v)
         throws IVisitor.VisitorException
        The accept method corresponding the IVisitor, to be implemented in each subclass as { return v.visit(this); }
        Type Parameters:
        T - the return type desired from the visit methods

        Returns:
        the value returned by the visit method
        Throws:
